The paper focuses on a large-scale dataset for reading comprehension that requires commonsense-based reasoning, which is a topic that falls under natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also experiments with state-of-the-art neural architectures for reading comprehension, which falls under machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), specifically in the sub-fields of computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) as well. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
